an><span style="color:#222222; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Airey</span><span style="color:#222222; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> v Ireland</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> Series A, No.32,(1979-80) </span><span style="color:#222222; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">(1979) 2 EHRR 305.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn9"></a><a href="#_ftnref9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> If the work on a case exceeds three times the nominal number of hours represented by the fixed fee, it is paid at an hourly rate.  This is known as reaching the “escape” threshold.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn10"></a><a href="#_ftnref10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> See </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Category Definitions</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> therein.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn11"></a><a href="#_ftnref11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> (1979-80) 2 EHRR 305</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn12"></a><a href="#_ftnref12">[12]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> (2002) 35 EH</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">RR 31</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn13"></a><a href="#_ftnref13">[13]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">See </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Transforming Legal Aid: next steps</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">, </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans