 and</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> subsequently won his application to be allowed to stay.  He gave evidence for the Crown in a trial in which a gang leader was convicted for murder.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn17"></a><a href="#_ftnref17">[17]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> Annexe K, paragraph 4.1.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn18"></a><a href="#_ftnref18">[18]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> No Recourse to Public Funds Network: </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Shadow Impact Assessment and Shadow </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Financial Impact Assessment</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">, with Annexes, available at </span><a href="http://www.nrpfnetwork.org.uk/policy/Pages/default.aspx"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.nrpfnetwork.org.uk/policy/Pages/default.aspx</span></a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn19"></a><a href="#_ftnref19">[19]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> See </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Boultif</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> v. Switzerland</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">(no. 54273/00); </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Ma</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">slov</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> v. Austria</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">(applic</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">ation no. 1638/03). </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Moustaquim</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> v Belgium</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">(Application no. 12313/86)</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn20"></a><a href="#_ftnref20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Maouiaa</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> v France</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">Application 39652/98 [2000] ECHR 455 (5 October 2000)</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn21"></a><a href="#_ftnref21">[21]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> British and EEA passports are not stamped on entry to or exit from the UK. A person who has made an application to the Home Office for an extension of leave before their leave expired but who has not received a decision on that application before the date</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> on which their leave would otherwise have expired will benefit from leave under s 3C of the Immigration Act 1971.  Such persons may be able to show nothing but a copy of a document that appears to confirm that their leave has run out. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">The Home Affairs Sel</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">ect Committee’s March 2013 report </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Work of the UK Border Agency</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">, HC 792,</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> identified that some 55,000 applications had not been put onto the Home Office database which would thus not yield an accurate answer about status were it possible to check it.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn22"></a><a href="#_ftnref22">[22]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> See F</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">ootnote 30 in the consultation paper.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn23"></a><a href="#_ftnref23">[23]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">Available at </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.ukba.homeoffice.gov.uk/sitecontent/documents/employersandsponsors/preventingillegalworking/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.ukba.homeoffice.gov.uk/sitecontent/documents/employersandsponsors/preventing</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">illegalworking/</span></a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn24"></a><a href="#_ftnref24">[24]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Comprehensive guidance for employers on preventing illegal working</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">, June 2012.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn25"></a><a href="#_ftnref25">[25]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> The Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punis</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">hment of Offenders Act, </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">Sched</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> 1, Part 1, paragraphs 25 to 27.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn26"></a><a href="#_ftnref26">[26]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> The Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">Act, </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">Sched</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> 1, Part 1, paragraph 24.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn27"></a><a href="#_ftnref27">[27]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> The Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act, </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">Sched</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> 1, Part 1, paragraphs 28 to 29.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn28"></a><a href="#_ftnref28">[28]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> The Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act, Schedule 1, Part 1, paragraph 32.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn29"></a><a href="#_ftnref29">[29]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> HL Report, </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">5 Mar 2012: Columns 1569-1572.  See also </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">HL Re</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">port 27 Mar 2012: Column 1253.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn30"></a><a href="#_ftnref30">[30]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> Human Rights Act 1998, s 7(5).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn31"></a><a href="#_ftnref31">[31]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> In the limited sense described below. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn32"></a><a href="#_ftnref32">[32]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> At paragraph 3.55</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn33"></a><a href="#_ftnref33">[33]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> Paragraph 118</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn34"></a><a href="#_ftnref34">[34]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> Paragraph 2.15</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn35"></a><a href="#_ftnref35">[35]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> HC 395, paragraphs 400ff.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn36"></a><a href="#_ftnref36">[36]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="color:#222222; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">Regulation 2003/343</span><span style="color:#222222; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">/EC.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn37"></a><a href="#_ftnref37">[37]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">MB et ors</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> v Secretary of State</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> [2013] EWHC 123 (Admin).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn38"></a><a href="#_ftnref38">[38]</a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">Asylum and Immigration (Treatment of Claimants Act, etc.) Act 2004, </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10pt">sched</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:10